  "answer": "The following works in the corpus discuss the Shudra (also spelled Śūdra), identified explicitly as the lowest *varṇa*, in the context of *dharma*, duties, punishments, inheritance, marriage, and social hierarchy:\n\n- *Bṛhaspati Smṛti*[^1]\n- *Kātyāyana Smṛti*[^2]\n- *Manusmṛti*[^3]\n\nNo other works in the corpus mention the Shudra directly.[^4]\n\n[^1]: *Bṛhaspati Smṛti*, [Chapter 1, p-90a287](/works/unknown-brhaspati-smrti-0fd070/01/translation/#p-90a287/).\n\n[^2]: *Kātyāyana Smṛti*, [Chapter 7, p-ea58aa](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/07/translation/#p-ea58aa/).\n\n[^3]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 1, p-13a2db](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-13a2db/).\n\n[^4]: Exhaustive searches of the English translations for \"Sudra\", \"Shudra\", \"Sudras\", and \"\"lowest varna\"\" returned zero results outside these works.",
